Datei: keycloak-extension/src/main/java/dev/authsandbox/keycloak/LoginTokenAuthenticator.java

### Was entfällt komplett:
- HttpClient und jwksCache (ConcurrentHashMap) — beide Felder und alle Nutzungen entfernen
- Methoden: fetchJwks(), parseJwk(), getPublicKey(), validateJwt(), findIdpByIssuer(), getClientJwksUrl(), getTrustedClientIds(), isTrustedClient()
- Die innere Klasse CachedJWKSet (Zeilen 348-364) — komplett entfernen
- Die io.jsonwebtoken.*-Imports

### Neue Implementierung authenticate():

1. login_token aus auth session lesen (wie bisher):
   String loginToken = context.getAuthenticationSession().getClientNote("client_request_param_login_token");
   if (loginToken == null || loginToken.isBlank()) → context.failure(INVALID_CREDENTIALS)

2. login_token dekodieren (Base64-URL → JSON):
   byte[] jsonBytes = Base64.getUrlDecoder().decode(loginToken);
   Map<String,String> token = new ObjectMapper().readValue(jsonBytes, Map.class);
   String sub = token.get("sub");
   String encryptedKey = token.get("encryptedKey");
   String encryptedData = token.get("encryptedData");
   String iv = token.get("iv");
   String signature = token.get("signature");

3. User via sub (= userId = Keycloak username) suchen:
   RealmModel realm = session.getContext().getRealm();
   UserModel user = session.users().getUserByUsername(realm, sub);
   if (user == null) → context.failure(INVALID_USER)
   if (!user.isEnabled()) → context.failure(USER_DISABLED)

4. device-login Credential laden:
   DeviceCredentialModel credential = user.credentialManager()
       .getStoredCredentialsByTypeStream(DeviceCredentialModel.TYPE)
       .map(DeviceCredentialModel::createFromCredentialModel)
       .findFirst()
       .orElse(null);
   if (credential == null) → context.failure(INVALID_CREDENTIALS)

5. Hybrid-Decrypt:
   // encPrivKey aus secretData (PKCS#8 DER Base64)
   byte[] encPrivKeyBytes = Base64.getDecoder().decode(credential.getEncPrivKey());
   PrivateKey encPrivKey = KeyFactory.getInstance("RSA")
       .generatePrivate(new PKCS8EncodedKeySpec(encPrivKeyBytes));

   // AES-Key entschlüsseln
   Cipher rsaCipher = Cipher.getInstance("RSA/ECB/OAEPWithSHA-256AndMGF1Padding");
   rsaCipher.init(Cipher.DECRYPT_MODE, encPrivKey);
   byte[] aesKeyBytes = rsaCipher.doFinal(Base64.getDecoder().decode(encryptedKey));

   // Payload entschlüsseln
   SecretKey aesKey = new SecretKeySpec(aesKeyBytes, "AES");
   Cipher aesCipher = Cipher.getInstance("AES/GCM/NoPadding");
   byte[] ivBytes = Base64.getDecoder().decode(iv);
   aesCipher.init(Cipher.DECRYPT_MODE, aesKey, new GCMParameterSpec(128, ivBytes));
   byte[] payloadBytes = aesCipher.doFinal(Base64.getDecoder().decode(encryptedData));
   String payloadJson = new String(payloadBytes, StandardCharsets.UTF_8);

6. Payload parsen:
   Map<String,Object> payload = new ObjectMapper().readValue(payloadJson, Map.class);
   String payloadUserId = (String) payload.get("userId");
   String payloadNonce = (String) payload.get("nonce");
   long payloadExp = ((Number) payload.get("exp")).longValue();

7. Validierung:
   // exp prüfen
   if (Instant.now().getEpochSecond() > payloadExp) → context.failure(EXPIRED_CODE)

   // userId == sub prüfen
   if (!sub.equals(payloadUserId)) → context.failure(INVALID_CREDENTIALS)

   // Nonce Replay-Schutz via SingleUseObjectProvider
   SingleUseObjectProvider singleUseProvider = session.getProvider(SingleUseObjectProvider.class);
   long ttl = Math.max(1, payloadExp - Instant.now().getEpochSecond());
   boolean wasNotUsed = singleUseProvider.putIfAbsent("logintoken-nonce:" + payloadNonce, ttl);
   if (!wasNotUsed) → context.failure(INVALID_CREDENTIALS)

   // Signatur prüfen: SHA256withRSA über encryptedData mit App Public Key aus credentialData
   byte[] pubKeyBytes = Base64.getDecoder().decode(
       credential.getPublicKey()
           .replace("-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----", "")
           .replace("-----END PUBLIC KEY-----", "")
           .replaceAll("\\s", ""));
   PublicKey appPubKey = KeyFactory.getInstance("RSA")
       .generatePublic(new X509EncodedKeySpec(pubKeyBytes));
   Signature sig = Signature.getInstance("SHA256withRSA");
   sig.initVerify(appPubKey);
   sig.update(Base64.getDecoder().decode(encryptedData));
   boolean valid = sig.verify(Base64.getUrlDecoder().decode(signature));
   if (!valid) → context.failure(INVALID_CREDENTIALS)

8. Erfolg:
   context.setUser(user);
   context.success();

